title: Audiblesync:
content:
Audible Sync: until a couple of days ago have happily used audible sync to download and install talking books on a sandisk MP3 player: In the middle of listening to an older MP3 it decided that it needed to be activated. I was unable to activate device. Ended up re installing the app. A new MP3 was activiated. Now though the app is unable to download any books from the website! Keeps telling me there is a problem. At one point was seemingly unable to download and then reinstall the audiblesync app. Then discovered an update from Microsoft had stopped the installation of any app that wasn't from their store. This issue is now rectified.

Have consulted Audible help! Followed all their advice with no result. Awaiting further possible solutions. I wondered if there might be anything via the mozilla/ firefox browser that could be preventing the download. As you may tell am exploring all options. I listen to talking books ALL the time. Would appreciate any ideas. do hope this makes sense.
creator: crossmoyle7

title: What could possibly mess up my javascript tooltip windows after updating from 106 to 118.0.2?
content:
I have a script that shows tooltips when you hover with a mouse pointer on an element. It worked before I updated to 108.0.2. I then updated to the current version (119.0.1) in hopes to fix the problem, but still no tooltips show up. I wonder why. Do you have any idea?

P.S. In the "load" event handler (this is when the window loads) I add mouse event handlers to "A" elements to catch "mouseenter, mouseleave," and "mousemove" events. Then, in the same "load" event handler, I create invisible "SPAN" element that would serve as a tooltip. I then add this invisible element to the "BODY" using "document.body.insertAdjacentElement('beforeend', ..." The event handlers for mouse events change the "style.display" property of the tooltip element to render it visible or vice versa, depending on where the mouse pointer is. Nothing fancy.

Thanks
creator: antizilla
